+Welcome to the stone age of software, where your trusty 386 processor struggles
+to keep up and floppy disks are still considered high-tech. This document
+lists the bare minimum software versions needed to compile the Linux kernel
+— because if you’re still running GCC 4.8, congratulations, you’re officially
+living in a museum!
 
