 Current Minimal Requirements
 ****************************
 
-Upgrade to at **least** these software revisions before thinking you've
-encountered a bug!  If you're unsure what version you're currently
-running, the suggested command should tell you.
+Upgrade to at **least** these software revisions before you start blaming
+the kernel for your problems! Unsure what version you're running? Use the
+commands below to find out.
 
-Again, keep in mind that this list assumes you are already functionally
-running a Linux kernel.  Also, not all tools are necessary on all
-systems; obviously, if you don't have any PC Card hardware, for example,
-you probably needn't concern yourself with pcmciautils.
+Keep in mind, this list assumes you’re already somehow running a Linux kernel.
+Not all tools are necessary on every system; for example, if you don’t have
+any PC Card hardware, feel free to ignore pcmciautils.
 
